!
! TABULATED QUANTITIES, TOTAL OF 2103 GOOD RELIABLE SOURCES:
!
!   NO ............ Source's running number .................................. sequential numbering
!   XCO_P ......... X-coordinate of current source ........................... (pixels) relative to the lower-left pixel (1,1)
!   YCO_P ......... Y-coordinate of current source ........................... (pixels) relative to the lower-left pixel (1,1)
!   WCS_ACOOR ..... WCS (J2000) alpha-coordinate of current source ........... (degrees)
!   WCS_DCOOR ..... WCS (J2000) delta-coordinate of current source ........... (degrees)
!   SIG_GLOB ...... Global detection significance over all wavelengths ....... SIG_GLOB=sqrt(sum(SIG_MONO#^2))
!   FG ............ Flag identifying global properties over all wavelengths .. see definitions below
!   GOOD .......... Global goodness combining SIG_GLOB and SNR_GLOB .......... GOOD=min{(SIG_GLOB*min{SNR_GLOB,1}/SEGM_ELONG/SOURCE_ELONG)/STENTATIVE,9.99}
!   SIG_MONO ...... Detection significance from monochromatic single scales .. SSPEAK/STDEV ~ single-scale analog of S/N ratio
!   FM ............ Flag identifying monochromatic properties ................ see definitions below
!   FXP_BEST ...... Estimate of peak flux for current source ................. (Jy/beam_obs)
!   FXP_ERRO ...... Estimate of peak flux error for current source ........... (Jy/beam_obs)
!   FXT_BEST ...... Estimate of total flux for current source ................ (Jy)
!   FXT_ERRO ...... Estimate of total flux error for current source .......... (Jy)
!   AFWHM ......... Major size estimate (FWHM) for current source ............ (arcsec)
!   BFWHM ......... Minor size estimate (FWHM) for current source ............ (arcsec)
!   THEPA ......... Major axis rotation angle (east of the vertical axis) .... (degrees) position angle PA=THEPA_MOM+30.00 (east of north)
!
! DEFINITIONS AND COMMENTS:
!
!  1. Catalog entries may have a value of 0.000E+00 for sources outside the observational mask.
!  2. SIG_MONO# has a special value of 9.999E-31 if a source is not visible in clean single scales.
!  3. FX*_BEST# and FX*_ERRO# have a special value of 9.999E-31 if their measurements are < 1.0E-30.
!  4. Monochromatic S/N ratio can be computed from the data columns: SNR_MONO#=FXP_BEST#/FXP_ERRO#.
!  5. Global S/N ratio is defined similarly to SIG_GLOB: SNR_GLOB=sqrt(sum(SNR_MONO#^2)).
!  6. Source is considered tentative when 3.5<SIG_MONO#<7 at all wavelengths used in detection.
!  7. Global goodness GOOD is negative (multiplied by -1) only to indicate tentative sources.
!  8. One should always use only sources with GOOD>1~3: small values may indicate spurious sources.
!  9. Meaning of the global flag FG:
!     FG=0 ...... isolated source (not blended with any other source in any waveband)
!     FG=1 ...... blended source (footprints intersect by more than 20% in at least one waveband)
!     FG=2 ...... sub-structured source (inner 25% area of its footprint contains an entire footprint of at least one source)
!     FG=3 ...... sub-structuring source (causing a larger source to be flagged as sub-structured)
! 10. Meaning of the monochromatic flag FM (negative if deblending iterations have not converged):
!     FM#=  0 ... no problems identified for the source at this wavelength #
!     FM#=  1 ... larger than its characteristic scale size: AFWHM#>max{OBSBEAM#,SCALE#,APERTURE#}
!     FM#=  2 ... larger than the desired maximum of [13 152 171 191 177 155 161 149] arcsec: AFWHM#>max{SRCMAXSIZE#,APERTURE#}
!     FM#=  3 ... larger than both the characteristic size and the desired maximum size or aperture
!     FM#= 10 ... peak intensity is not measurable: FXP_BEST#/FXP_ERRO#<1.0
!     FM#= 20 ... total flux is not measurable: FXT_BEST#/FXT_ERRO#<1.0
!     FM#= 30 ... both total flux and peak intensity are not measurable
!     FM#=100 ... sub-structured (the inner 25% area of its footprint contains an entire footprint of at least one measurable source)
!     FM#=200 ... significance is low: SIG_MONO#<3.5
!  __________________________________________________________________
! |                                                                  |
! |  NEVER USE ALL SOURCES FROM MULTI-WAVELENGTH CATALOGS BLINDLY!   |
! |  Select (and use) only significant sources in each waveband, on  |
! |  the basis of quantities provided in the catalog. Those are the  |
! |  global significance SIG_GLOB, global flag FG and goodness GOOD, |
! |  monochromatic significance SIG_MONO and flag FM, as well as the |
! |  S/N ratios FXP_BEST/FXP_ERRO, FXT_BEST/FXT_ERRO, and possibly   |
! |  the measured sizes AFWHM, BFWHM in one or more wavebands.       |
! |__________________________________________________________________|
